tafsir[17]{c,v,t}:
  87,18,"These instructions and stories that I mentioned to you are in the scriptures revealed before you."
  87,19,"These are the scriptures revealed to Abraham and Moses (peace be upon them)."
  88,2,"People on the day of judgment will either be wretched or fortunate. The faces of the wretched will be humiliated and downcast."
  88,3,"Tired and strained due to the chains that they will be dragged by and the shackles that they will be tied with."
  88,4,"Those faces will enter a hot fire to suffer from its heat."
  88,5,"They will be given to drink from a spring with extremely hot water."
  88,7,"It does not nourish the one who eats it nor does it satiate his hunger."
  88,10,"In a Paradise elevated in position and rank."
  88,12,"In this Paradise there are flowing springs that they will make flow and direct however they wish."
  88,13,"In it are high couches."
  88,14,"And cups laid out and ready for drinking."
  88,15,"In it are cushions packed closely to one another."
  88,16,"In it are carpets spread out here and there."
  88,22,"You have not been given control over them so that you can compel them to have faith."
  88,24,"Allah will punish them on the Day of Judgement with the greatest punishment by entering them into Hell to remain there forever."
  88,25,"To Me alone is their return after their death."
  88,26,"Then it is My duty alone to call them to account for their actions. This is not for you or anyone besides you."